## Pages

### Profile
- Left ~40%: square profile image area (up to 700×700px, responsive). 4px gap below it, then the **Image upload** button (gray).
- Profile image: upload, replace, save. Show an immediate local preview of a newly chosen image before saving.
- **Resume: upload, replace, save — with an inline preview.**
  - Accept `.pdf`, `.png`, `.jpg`, `.jpeg`, `.webp`.
  - On selecting a file (before saving) **and** when an existing resume is loaded, render a **preview**:
    - Image file → thumbnail `<img>` (max-height ~380px, contained).
    - PDF file → embedded `<iframe>` preview (~420px tall, white background).
    - Other/unknown → fallback "open file" link.
  - Also show an "Open in new tab" link for the stored resume.
- **본인 이름**, **한줄 소개**, **관심 분야**: single-line white text inputs, editable and saved.
- All Profile data persists to the `profile` table; image/resume to Storage. On save failure, keep inputs and clean up any just-uploaded files.

### Portfolio (default landing — and the logo's home target)
- Pinterest-style responsive **masonry** grid; show the grid immediately.
- **Card width: narrow and uniform** (~240px). **Card height varies per item, following the media's natural aspect ratio** (true masonry — staggered heights, no fixed/cropped card height). Each card shows cover image, title, author.
- **Hover interaction:**
  - On hover over a card's media, change the overlay shading (smooth dark overlay transition) to signal interactivity.
  - If the card's media is a **video**, it **auto-plays on hover** (muted, looped, inline) and pauses/resets when the pointer leaves.
- Posts with **video only** (no image) must still render as cards (use the video frame as the cover).
- **Card click → detail modal** (polished, gallery-style):
  - Shows title (bold, ~24px), author rendered as muted "by {author}", content, and the generation prompt in a soft rounded card with an uppercase letter-spaced "GENERATION PROMPT" label.
  - Media priority: an uploaded/direct video (`posts.video_url`) plays via `<video controls>`; otherwise a `posts.youtube_url` plays via a responsive 16:9 YouTube `<iframe>` embed; otherwise show the image with rounded top corners. (On portfolio cards, a YouTube post uses its thumbnail `https://img.youtube.com/vi/{id}/hqdefault.jpg` as the cover; the full player opens in the modal.)
  - **No empty media gap:** hide the media area entirely when there is no media, and remove broken images on error (`onerror`) so hotlink-blocked URLs don't leave blank space. Empty author/content/tags collapse rather than leaving gaps. Trim leading/trailing whitespace on all text.
  - A floating round **×** close button sits at the top-right; **Edit** and **Delete** (gray) are right-aligned in the footer.
  - Subtle entrance: backdrop fade + a gentle pop/scale-in. Rounded corners (~20px), deep shadow, max-width ~680px.

### Create — Post CRUD (implement in code)
**Create form fields**: title, content, author, image file, **MP4 video file _or_ a pasted video URL**, and a dedicated **Generation Prompt** input area (multi-line textarea, persists to `posts.prompt`).
- **Video input — file or URL:** accept either an uploaded `.mp4` file **or** a pasted video URL.
  - A pasted **YouTube** link (watch / `youtu.be` / shorts / embed forms) is saved to `posts.youtube_url`; any other (direct) video link is saved to `posts.video_url`.
  - A freshly uploaded file wins and supersedes any previous URL (clear the other column on save).
  - On edit, surface an existing URL (YouTube or pasted direct link) in the URL field so it can be changed; uploaded files show a "(current video kept)" note.
- Either an image **or** an MP4 is enough to save (image-less, video-only posts allowed).
- On save: upload files to Storage, store public URLs in `posts`.
- If saving fails, **keep the entered text and selected files** and clean up any just-uploaded files. Reset the form **only on success**.

**Update (edit) — optimized screen flow:**
- Entering edit (from the modal's **Edit**) loads the post into the Create form, switches to the Create page, and **scrolls to the top** so the form is in view.
- Show an **edit-mode banner** ("Editing post. Saving will update the existing post. Choosing a new image/video replaces it; leave empty to keep current media."), change the heading to **Edit Post**, and change the submit button to **Update**.
- A **Cancel edit** button resets the form and returns to Portfolio.
- Selecting a new image/MP4 replaces the existing URL; no new file keeps the existing media.
- **On successful create or update:** reset the form, return to **Portfolio**, and **scroll to the top** for a clean landing. On failure, keep inputs and show the error inline.

**Delete**: confirm dialog first, then delete the row from `posts`.

## Media handling
- Images: `.png`, `.jpg`, `.jpeg`, `.webp`. Videos: `.mp4` only. Resume: `.pdf`, `.png`, `.jpg`, `.jpeg`, `.webp`.
- Single public bucket `portfolio-media`, separated by path:
  - post images → `images/`
  - post videos → `videos/`
  - profile image → `profile/image/`
  - resume → `resumes/`
- Save returned public URLs to `posts.image_url`, `posts.video_url`, `profile.profile_image_url`, `profile.resume_url`.
- If the DB write fails after upload, delete the just-uploaded file from Storage (cleanup).
- New video **file uploads** and **direct video URLs** go to `posts.video_url`. **YouTube URLs** go to `posts.youtube_url` and render as an embedded player.

## Supabase SQL — run once (idempotent)
```sql
-- UUID helper
create extension if not exists "pgcrypto";

-- posts
create table if not exists posts (
  id uuid primary key default gen_random_uuid(),
  title text not null,
  content text,
  author text,
  image_url text,
  video_url text,
  youtube_url text,
  prompt text,
  created_at timestamp with time zone default now()
);
alter table posts
  add column if not exists content text,
  add column if not exists author text,
  add column if not exists image_url text,
  add column if not exists video_url text,
  add column if not exists youtube_url text,
  add column if not exists prompt text,
  add column if not exists created_at timestamp with time zone default now();
alter table posts enable row level security;
drop policy if exists "Public can read posts" on posts;
create policy "Public can read posts" on posts for select using (true);
drop policy if exists "Public can insert posts" on posts;
create policy "Public can insert posts" on posts for insert with check (true);
drop policy if exists "Public can update posts" on posts;
create policy "Public can update posts" on posts for update using (true) with check (true);
drop policy if exists "Public can delete posts" on posts;
create policy "Public can delete posts" on posts for delete using (true);

-- profile
create table if not exists profile (
  id uuid primary key default gen_random_uuid(),
  name text,
  bio text,
  interests text,
  profile_image_url text,
  resume_url text,
  created_at timestamp with time zone default now(),
  updated_at timestamp with time zone default now()
);
alter table profile
  add column if not exists name text,
  add column if not exists bio text,
  add column if not exists interests text,
  add column if not exists profile_image_url text,
  add column if not exists resume_url text,
  add column if not exists created_at timestamp with time zone default now(),
  add column if not exists updated_at timestamp with time zone default now();
create or replace function set_updated_at()
returns trigger as $$
begin
  new.updated_at = now();
  return new;
end;
$$ language plpgsql;
drop trigger if exists set_profile_updated_at on profile;
create trigger set_profile_updated_at
before update on profile
for each row execute function set_updated_at();
alter table profile enable row level security;
drop policy if exists "Public can read profile" on profile;
create policy "Public can read profile" on profile for select using (true);
drop policy if exists "Public can insert profile" on profile;
create policy "Public can insert profile" on profile for insert with check (true);
drop policy if exists "Public can update profile" on profile;
create policy "Public can update profile" on profile for update using (true) with check (true);
drop policy if exists "Public can delete profile" on profile;
create policy "Public can delete profile" on profile for delete using (true);

-- storage bucket
insert into storage.buckets (id, name, public)
values ('portfolio-media', 'portfolio-media', true)
on conflict (id) do update set public = true;

-- storage policies
drop policy if exists "Public can read portfolio media" on storage.objects;
create policy "Public can read portfolio media" on storage.objects for select using (bucket_id = 'portfolio-media');
drop policy if exists "Public can upload portfolio media" on storage.objects;
create policy "Public can upload portfolio media" on storage.objects for insert with check (bucket_id = 'portfolio-media');
drop policy if exists "Public can update portfolio media" on storage.objects;
create policy "Public can update portfolio media" on storage.objects for update using (bucket_id = 'portfolio-media') with check (bucket_id = 'portfolio-media');
drop policy if exists "Public can delete portfolio media" on storage.objects;
create policy "Public can delete portfolio media" on storage.objects for delete using (bucket_id = 'portfolio-media');
```


